          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a kind of manual or treatise used for consultation and is a text on the rules (religious laws) governing the removal of impurities, especially those related to pregnancy.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Āśaucanirṇaya</title>
              <author>Tryaṃbaka Paṇḍita</author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrī āṃgirasamudgalakulajaladhisudhāṃśupadavākyapramāṇapārāvārapārīṇayāyajūkaśiro-ratnanārāyaṇātmajaraghunāthasūrisūnutryaṃbakapaṃḍitaviracitāśaucanirṇayaḥ samāptaḥ // śrīrāmārpaṇam astu // saṃvat 1934 śakaḥ 1799 āṣāḍhakṛṣṇa 7 bhaume idaṃ tryaṃbakīyāśaucanirṇayapustakaṃ samāptam // śrīrāmacaṃdrārpaṇam astu // (f. 7r).</colophon>
